  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly:  "Epigram poet in the early 1st cent. AD (cf. Anth. Pal. 7,391 on the death of Germanicus in AD 19), born perhaps in Smyrna
      (according to the lemma of Anth. Pal. 11,72; the poem's authorship is, however, not certain). At least nine poems by B. are extant from the &#x2018;Garland&#x2019; of Philippus (with the
      addition of several incerta, cf. Anth. Pal. 9,30 as well), all of which rather mediocre..."  "Bassus Lollius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and ; Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2011. Brill Online. 
      Tufts University Library. 25 April 2011 </mads:note>
